node.text:
I was working in the Glenfield Mall in Auckland, New Zealand. It was all over the news. The images were frightening. As a 19year old, I couldn’t at the time, fathom the significance of what was happening. Years later, I’d marry a man who lived in NYC at the time. Who almost lost his best friend in the south tower. He has told me stories of that day and what he saw. Deep down, I’m always grateful he was no where near the towers. 

Remembering those who lost their lives that day and later. Remembering the innocent lives lost in the wars that followed. Sending love to all families who live with the loss. Sending love to those who survived and who relive it and love to those who demonstrated Ubuntu, banding together and helping one another. I love you NY ❤️ #neverforget ( I hate that I have to write this.  There are actual people truly affected by the events of 20 years ago. If you cannot be respectful, scroll by or unfollow).
